</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-80_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Integrating clinical effectiveness into the broader clinical governance framework creates a dynamic synergy that propels healthcare quality forward. Clinical effectiveness provides the evidence-based foundation for clinical governance activities, ensuring that efforts to improve healthcare quality are grounded in the best available evidence.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-82_">Enhancing patient outcomes through evidence-based care
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-84_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The primary aim of integrating clinical effectiveness with clinical governance is to enhance patient outcomes. By ensuring that healthcare interventions are effective and efficiently managed, patients receive care that is based on the latest evidence and delivered in a safe, coordinated, and patient-centred manner.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-86_">Driving quality improvement
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-88_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Clinical effectiveness acts as a catalyst for quality improvement within the clinical governance framework. Through the continual evaluation of clinical practices against evidence-based standards, healthcare organisations can identify areas for improvement, implement changes, and monitor the impact of these changes on patient outcomes.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-90_">Reducing variability in care
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-92_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">One of the challenges in healthcare is the variability in the quality and effectiveness of care provided to patients. By embedding clinical effectiveness within clinical governance, healthcare organisations can standardise care processes based on evidence-based guidelines, reducing unwarranted variations in care and ensuring that all patients receive the highest standard of care.
