</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-0691" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-uojGG hMqLeX pf-139_ pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-ilfuhL bpQaoh"><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-140_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-141_"><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-142_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the vast and intricate healthcare landscape, the twin pillars of clinical effectiveness and clinical governance stand as beacons of excellence, guiding the delivery of superior patient care. Together, they form a synergistic relationship that enhances the quality of healthcare services and ensures these services are provided in a safe, evidence-based, and patient-centred. This blog explores the critical interplay between clinical effectiveness and governance, illustrating how their integration is pivotal in driving healthcare quality to new heights.<br><br>In this blog&nbsp;<a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a>&nbsp;explores the critical interplay between clinical effectiveness and governance, illustrating how their integration is pivotal in driving healthcare quality to new heights.
